Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed ExtraLight Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed ExtraLight Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed ExtraLight'.

Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensed', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed'.

Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed Medium Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedMedium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedMedium', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed Medium Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-SemiCondensedMedium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed Medium' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed Medium'.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed Bold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Bold'.

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiCondensed ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiCondensed ExtraBold'.
